Enugu State House of Assembly yesterday approved a request by Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi to appoint 15 Special Advisers (SAs). Speaker of the Enugu State House of Assembly, Hon. Edward Ubosi read the message brought to the assembly by Ugwuanyi for approval and consideration on the floor of the House. Ubosi said that Ugwuanyi urged the assembly members to approve the appointment of the special advisers to enable him discharge his duties creditably. The leader of the House, Hon. Ikechukwu Ezeugwu, moved a motion for the acceptance and approval of the governorâ€™s request and urged his colleagues to honour it. Ezeugwu referred members to Section 196 subSections 2 and 3 of the 1999 Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria as amended, saying that the governor of a state had powers to appoint any person to assist him in the performance of his duty. The leader said that Section 2 stated that the number of advisers, their remuneration and allowances should be as prescribed by law or by resolution of the state house of assembly. He moved a motion that pursuant to the section, the house should approve the appointment of fifteen special advisers to assist governor in discharge of the duty while the deputy leader, Mrs. Onyinye Ugwu seconded the motion.
In a related development, the speaker, Hon. Ubosi set up a committee for the selection of the heads of the various standing committees of the House. Deputy speaker of the assembly, Hon. Ugwu Callistus, Udi North was appointed chairman while the leader of the House, Hon. Ikechukwu Ezeugwu, Hon. Iloabuchi Aniagu, Nkanu West; Hon. Jane Eneh, the Chief Whip and Hon. Emma Ugwuaruh, Nsukka West respectively were appointed as members.
The committee was given one week to submit its report while the assembly was adjourned to 2nd July, 2019.